beastiary:int_hermaphrodite_plato a beast:Interpretation ;
    rdfs:comment "In Plato interpretation of the hermaphrodite, two opposites, men and women, share the same body forming a union. Eventually they are punished and separated through a traumatic cut, which lead the two parts to search for one another for the rest of their lives, recalling the mystical structure described by Durand."@en ;
