beastiary:archetype_abandoned_child a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "The exposed or forsaken infant, left to fate yet often marked for a special destiny."@en ;
    beast:relatedTo beastiary:archetype_shameful_offspring .

beastiary:archetype_cosmic a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "The universal principle or force operating on a cosmic scale, beyond the human."@en .

beastiary:archetype_divided_self a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "A figure torn between animal impulse and human consciousness, embodying the internal conflict between instinct and reason."@en .

beastiary:archetype_divine_punishment a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "Retribution inflicted by the gods for transgression, the sacred sanction against hubris."@en .

beastiary:archetype_metamorphosis a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "The principle of transformation and change of form as such."@en .

beastiary:archetype_semi_divine a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "Represents immortal beings, of noble character and superior skills."@en .

beastiary:archetype_sublime a beast:Archetype ;
    beast:hasMeaning "The fusion of terror and beauty into an overwhelming aesthetic."@en .

