beastiary:int_centaur_ovid a beast:Interpretation ;
    rdfs:comment "\"Eurytus and the centaurs in Ovid embody teriomorphic chaos as the instigators of the Centauromachia: the bestial appetite triggered by wine erupts into collective violence. The general fall from human rationality into bestial behavior represents also catamorphic descent, the degradation of the hybrid form downward into pure animal impulse."@en ;
    beast:appearsIn beastiary:source_ovidius_metamorphoses ;
    beast:belongsToImaginaryStructure beast:SchizomorphicStructure ;
    beast:embodiesArchetype beastiary:archetype_predatory_lust,
        beastiary:archetype_raw_instinct,
        beastiary:archetype_violence ;
    beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol beast:CatamorphicSymbol,
        beast:TeriomorphicSymbol ;
    beast:hasNarrativeFunction beastiary:function_instigator ;
    beast:hasPersonalName "Eurytus"^^xsd:string ;
    beast:hasTextualReference beastiary:citation_ovid_met_12 ;
    beast:isGovernedBy beast:DiurnalRegime ;
    beast:ofCreature beastiary:creature_centaur .

beastiary:int_chimera_esiodo a beast:Interpretation ;
    rdfs:comment "Hesiod places the chimera among the monstrous, shameful offspring of Typhon and Echidna, a primordial and violent chaos-being whose fire-breathing, multi-headed body is teriomorphic terror in its most concentrated, genealogical form."@en ;
    beast:appearsIn beastiary:source_teogonia ;
    beast:belongsToImaginaryStructure beast:SchizomorphicStructure ;
    beast:embodiesArchetype beastiary:archetype_chaos,
        beastiary:archetype_shameful_offspring,
        beastiary:archetype_violence ;
    beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol beast:TeriomorphicSymbol ;
    beast:hasTextualReference beastiary:citation_esiodo_5 ;
    beast:isGovernedBy beast:DiurnalRegime ;
    beast:ofCreature beastiary:creature_chimera .

beastiary:int_giant_teogonia a beast:Interpretation ;
    beast:appearsIn beastiary:source_teogonia ;
    beast:hasTextualReference beastiary:citation_esiodo_1 ;
    beast:ofCreature beastiary:creature_giant .

beastiary:int_hermaphrodite_ovidius a beast:Interpretation ;
    rdfs:comment "Hermaphrodite is describe as a young man deprived from his masculinity becuase of his union with the nymph Salmace, who was desperately in love with him. This union happens inside a water source which traps him into a body with feminine characteristic, causing the loss of his masculine traits, adhering to the nyctomorphic symbolism of the mutilation."@en ;
    beast:appearsIn beastiary:source_ovidius_metamorphoses ;
    beast:belongsToImaginaryStructure beast:SchizomorphicStructure ;
    beast:embodiesArchetype beastiary:archetype_emasculation ;
    beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol beast:NyctomorphicSymbol ;
    beast:hasPersonalName "Hermaphrodite"^^xsd:string ;
    beast:hasTextualReference beastiary:citation_ovid_met_5 ;
    beast:isGovernedBy beast:DiurnalRegime ;
    beast:ofCreature beastiary:creature_hermaphrodite ;
    beast:removedPart beastiary:part_masculinity .

